page.title: 03RESIDENT BIRDS
page.content: Resident birds are fairly plentiful, blackbirds being the commonest. Five tit species, several finches,sparrows, starlings, dunnocks, yellow_hammers, linnets, wrens, robins, pied wag_ tails, song and mistle thrushes are most commonly seen. The green wood_ pecker is more common than the spotted variety. The following birds are seen occasionally:_ nut_hatch crossbills, tawny and little owls, partridge, tree_creepers and gold_crests Summer migrants include swallows, swifts, house_martins, willow warblers,andblack redstarts/ Winter migrants include redwings. field_ fares, siskins and starlings. During Autumn large flocks of lapwings gather in the fields. Crows, rooks, magpies and jackdaws are also common. Snip appear regularly in the coldest weather.
